#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Tāyanasutta "
msgstr "8. With Tāyana "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.49, sc1
msgctxt "sn2.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.8:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho tāyano devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the glorious god Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "

msgctxt "sn2.8:1.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho tāyano devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn2.8:2.1"
msgid "“Chinda sotaṃ parakkamma, "
msgstr "“Strive and cut the stream! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:2.2"
msgid "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; "
msgstr "Dispel sensual pleasures, brahmin. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:2.3"
msgid "Nappahāya munī kāme, "
msgstr "A sage who doesn’t give up sensual pleasures "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:2.4"
msgid "nekattamupapajjati. "
msgstr "is not reborn in a unified state. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.112, sc3
msgctxt "sn2.8:3.1"
msgid "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṃ, "
msgstr "If one is to do what should be done, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:3.2"
msgid "daḷhamenaṃ parakkame; "
msgstr "one should staunchly strive. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:3.3"
msgid "Sithilo hi paribbājo, "
msgstr "For the life gone forth when laxly led "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:3.4"
msgid "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṃ. "
msgstr "just stirs up dust all the more. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: dukkaṭaṃ → dukkataṃ (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.8:4.1"
msgid "Akataṃ dukkaṭaṃ seyyo, "
msgstr "It’s better to leave a bad deed undone—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:4.2"
msgid "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṃ; "
msgstr "later you burn for that misdeed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:4.3"
msgid "Katañca sukataṃ seyyo, "
msgstr "It’s better to do a good deed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:4.4"
msgid "yaṃ katvā nānutappati. "
msgstr "after which you’ll not regret. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn2.8:5.1"
msgid "Kuso yathā duggahito, "
msgstr "When kusa grass is wrongly grasped "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:5.2"
msgid "hatthamevānukantati; "
msgstr "it only cuts the hand. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:5.3"
msgid "Sāmaññaṃ dupparāmaṭṭhaṃ, "
msgstr "So too, the ascetic life, when wrongly taken, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:5.4"
msgid "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "drags you to hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn2.8:6.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kiñci sithilaṃ kammaṃ, "
msgstr "Any lax act, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:6.2"
msgid "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṃ vataṃ; "
msgstr "any corrupt observance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:6.3"
msgid "Saṅkassaraṃ brahmacariyaṃ, "
msgstr "or suspicious spiritual life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:6.4"
msgid "na taṃ hoti mahapphalan”ti. "
msgstr "is not very fruitful.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn2.8:7.1"
msgid "Idamavoca tāyano devaputto; "
msgstr "That’s what the god Tāyana said. "

msgctxt "sn2.8:7.2"
msgid "idaṃ vatvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.113, sc8
msgctxt "sn2.8:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had happened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.8:8.2"
msgid "“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ tāyano nāma devaputto purāṇatitthakaro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, tonight, the glorious god Tāyana, formerly a religious founder, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, "

msgctxt "sn2.8:8.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto mama santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "and recited these verses in my presence.” The Buddha repeated the verses in full, adding: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn2.8:9.1"
msgid "‘Chinda sotaṃ parakkamma, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:9.2"
msgid "kāme panuda brāhmaṇa; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:9.3"
msgid "Nappahāya munī kāme, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:9.4"
msgid "nekattamupapajjati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.50, sc10
msgctxt "sn2.8:10.1"
msgid "Kayirā ce kayirāthenaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:10.2"
msgid "daḷhamenaṃ parakkame; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:10.3"
msgid "Sithilo hi paribbājo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:10.4"
msgid "bhiyyo ākirate rajaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn2.8:11.1"
msgid "Akataṃ dukkaṭaṃ seyyo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:11.2"
msgid "pacchā tapati dukkaṭaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:11.3"
msgid "Katañca sukataṃ seyyo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:11.4"
msgid "yaṃ katvā nānutappati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn2.8:12.1"
msgid "Kuso yathā duggahito, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:12.2"
msgid "hatthamevānukantati; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:12.3"
msgid "Sāmaññaṃ dupparāmaṭṭhaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:12.4"
msgid "nirayāyūpakaḍḍhati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn2.8:13.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kiñci sithilaṃ kammaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:13.2"
msgid "saṅkiliṭṭhañca yaṃ vataṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:13.3"
msgid "Saṅkassaraṃ brahmacariyaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.8:13.4"
msgid "na taṃ hoti mahapphalan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.114, sc14
msgctxt "sn2.8:14.1"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, tāyano devaputto, idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. "
msgstr "“That’s what the god Tāyana said. Then he bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right side, before vanishing right there. "

msgctxt "sn2.8:14.2"
msgid "Uggaṇhātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; "
msgstr "Mendicants, learn the verses of Tāyana! "

msgctxt "sn2.8:14.3"
msgid "pariyāpuṇātha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā; "
msgstr "Memorize the verses of Tāyana! "

msgctxt "sn2.8:14.4"
msgid "dhāretha, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā. "
msgstr "Remember the verses of Tāyana! "

msgctxt "sn2.8:14.5"
msgid "Atthasaṃhitā, bhikkhave, tāyanagāthā ādibrahmacariyikā”ti. "
msgstr "These verses are beneficial and relate to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
